00:10:09,690 --> 00:10:12,340
绕过安理会实在是鲁莽之举
Going around the Security Council is a radical move.

171
00:10:12,390 --> 00:10:14,380
不是鲁莽  是有理有据
It's not radical, it's justified.

172
00:10:14,380 --> 00:10:16,390
你从旧纸堆里翻出60多年前的先例
You dust off some 60-year-old precedent

173
00:10:16,390 --> 00:10:17,710
还觉得是有理有据
and think you're justified?

174
00:10:18,060 --> 00:10:20,400
第377号决议案发动了一场战争
The Uniting for Peace resolution was used to start a war.

175
00:10:20,400 --> 00:10:22,180
那是为了阻止朝鲜的进攻
To end North Korea's aggression.

176
00:10:22,180 --> 00:10:23,200
文字游戏而已
Semantics.

177
00:10:24,560 --> 00:10:26,350
已经有93个国家支持这个决议案
Ninety-three nations on board already,

178
00:10:26,350 --> 00:10:28,510
还包括以色列  这可不是文字游戏
including Israel, that's not semantics.

179
00:10:28,510 --> 00:10:31,130
克莱尔  克里姆林宫给了我很大的压力
Claire, I'm getting a lot of pressure from the Kremlin.

180
00:10:31,130 --> 00:10:33,700
佩特罗夫不想闹到联合国大会上去
Petrov doesn't want this to go to the General Assembly.

181
00:10:33,700 --> 00:10:35,690
再给我点时间说服他
Give me a little more time to work on him.

182
00:10:46,700 --> 00:10:49,060
已经给你一个月了  我们要行动了
We've given you a month. We're moving forward.

183
00:10:57,740 --> 00:10:58,580
什么事
Yes?

184
00:10:58,580 --> 00:11:00,000
邓巴女士来了
Ms. Dunbar is here.

185
00:11:00,130 --> 00:11:01,060
让她进来
Send her in.

186
00:11:07,780 --> 00:11:09,370
{\pos(193.5,235.35)}{\pos(195.6,235.8)}古兰经

187
00:11:10,480 --> 00:11:11,140
希瑟
Heather.

188
00:11:11,140 --> 00:11:12,350
总统先生
Mr. President.

189
00:11:12,590 --> 00:11:14,500
我听了你今早辩护的音频
I listened to the audio of your defense this morning.

190
00:11:14,500 --> 00:11:15,790
表现很出色
It was outstanding.

191
00:11:15,790 --> 00:11:18,300
您说得没错  要打感情牌
You were right about making the emotional argument.

192
00:11:18,300 --> 00:11:21,730
我觉得这能让国家伤愈  请坐
I think it will help the country heal. Please, have a seat.

193
00:11:28,670 --> 00:11:31,850
我今晚还准备私下见默罕默德先生
I'm also going to meet later tonight with Mr. Mahmoud privately.

194
00:11:32,230 --> 00:11:33,910
亲自向他道歉
To personally apologize.

195
00:11:34,230 --> 00:11:36,100
这么做很有同情心
That's a compassionate thing to do.

196
00:11:38,310 --> 00:11:41,580
听你辩护时  我还注意到
When I listened to your argument, I also heard something else.

197
00:11:42,180 --> 00:11:43,980
雅各布斯法官曾质询你
There was a moment when Justice Jacobs

198
00:11:43,980 --> 00:11:46,260
无人机袭击的事
was asking you about drone strikes.

199
00:11:46,260 --> 00:11:47,610
是  我记得
Yeah, I remember.

200
00:11:47,770 --> 00:11:52,580
他停顿了...非常久
And he paused... for quite a long time.

201
00:11:53,500 --> 00:11:56,550
我觉得  他只是一时卡壳了
I think... he just lost his train of thought.

202
00:11:56,550 --> 00:11:57,350
好吧
Well...

203
00:12:02,410 --> 00:12:06,320
接下来我说的  一定要保密
What I'm about to tell you has to remain between us.

204
00:12:06,320 --> 00:12:07,340
没问题
Of course.

205
00:12:09,030 --> 00:12:11,910
雅各布斯法官有老年痴呆
Justice Jacobs has Alzheimer's.

206
00:12:12,590 --> 00:12:14,630
几个月前他告诉了我
He came to me a few months ago to tell me.

207
00:12:14,720 --> 00:12:16,370
现在还是早期
Now, it's in the early stages,

208
00:12:16,370 --> 00:12:19,540
除非有意观察  不然发现不了
so you wouldn't even notice unless you know what to look for.

209
00:12:20,140 --> 00:12:21,770
他还想待在法庭上吗
He wants to remain on the court?

210
00:12:21,770 --> 00:12:23,970
我要说的就是这个
Well, that's what I want to discuss.

211
00:12:24,780 --> 00:12:26,190
他想退休
He wanted to retire.

212
00:12:26,190 --> 00:12:28,660
我叫他再多等会儿
I asked him to hold on just a little while longer,

213
00:12:28,660 --> 00:12:32,380
让我先找到合适的人选  现在我找到了
until I could find a suitable replacement and now I have.

214
00:12:33,110 --> 00:12:36,310
我觉得...你最合适
And I want that replacement... to be you.

215
00:12:38,710 --> 00:12:39,750
你意下如何
What do you think?

216
00:12:43,260 --> 00:12:47,160
我...自愧不配  先生
I'm... humbled, sir.

217
00:12:47,160 --> 00:12:51,780
您愿考虑我  我着实震惊
And... honestly surprised that you'd consider me.

218
00:12:52,050 --> 00:12:53,170
为什么
Why is that?

219
00:12:53,170 --> 00:12:54,700
因为以前的纠葛
Given our history.

220
00:12:55,010 --> 00:12:57,440
我说过那些都过去了  就都过去了
When I said that was water under the bridge, I meant it.

221
00:12:57,440 --> 00:12:59,630
你有我国最强的法律头脑
You have the finest legal mind in this country,

222
00:12:59,630 --> 00:13:01,820
对宪法理解很透彻
a deep understanding of the Constitution,

223
00:13:01,820 --> 00:13:04,230
共和党不敢阻止你提名
and the Republicans wouldn't dare block your nomination.

224
00:13:04,230 --> 00:13:07,440
毕竟你检举过民主党的总统
After all, you prosecuted a Democratic president.

225
00:13:07,500 --> 00:13:09,770
当副检察长屈才了
You're too good to be Solicitor General.

226
00:13:09,890 --> 00:13:13,170
你要拿稳这个铁饭碗
Let's make sure you have a job for life.

227
00:13:14,260 --> 00:13:16,130
很感激您这么说  先生
I appreciate you saying that, sir.

228
00:13:17,620 --> 00:13:18,560
抱歉
I'm sorry.

229
00:13:19,950 --> 00:13:21,530
容我再考虑考虑
This is a lot to process.

230
00:13:21,530 --> 00:13:23,960
大选前就要搞定这事
It's important we do this before the election.

231
00:13:23,960 --> 00:13:26,620
共和党人当了总统就没准了
We could end up with a Republican president.

232
00:13:26,910 --> 00:13:28,790
除非你真想坐这个位置
And I don't want to suggest your name to Jacobs

233
00:13:28,790 --> 00:13:31,000
不然我不会向雅各布斯提你的名
unless you truly want the position.

234
00:13:31,740 --> 00:13:35,150
所以...现在就告诉我
So... I need to know now.

235
00:13:37,730 --> 00:13:40,610
好  我非常荣幸
Yes. It would be a great honor.

236
00:13:41,250 --> 00:13:43,240
很好  祝贺你
Good. Congratulations.

237
00:13:43,240 --> 00:13:45,040
你去告诉家人  我去跟雅各布斯说
You speak to your family. I'll speak to Jacobs.

238
00:13:45,040 --> 00:13:46,550
谢谢  总统先生
Thank you, Mr. President.

239
00:13:54,700 --> 00:13:56,240
{\pos(192.6,113.85)}带宽使用未授权

240
00:13:54,700 --> 00:13:56,240
{\pos(217.5,216.45)}{\pos(222.9,283.95)}注意  您已超过带宽授权限制  需要更高权限

241
00:14:27,170 --> 00:14:28,040
你看到了吗
Did you see this?

242
00:14:28,960 --> 00:14:29,550
看到什么
See what?

243
00:14:30,570 --> 00:14:31,870
我刚收到警告了
I just got an alert.

244
00:14:32,910 --> 00:14:35,450
不知道  我好一阵没见到吉姆了
I don't know. I haven't, uh... seen Jim in a while.

245
00:14:37,890 --> 00:14:38,870
真奇怪
That's weird.

246
00:14:47,970 --> 00:14:50,540
我想向你做出最诚挚的抱歉
I want to offer you my sincerest regret.

247
00:14:50,980 --> 00:14:53,700
希望你能够接受
And I hope that you will accept my apology.

248
00:14:54,030 --> 00:14:55,440
抱歉  我做不到
I'm sorry, but I can't.

249
00:14:57,030 --> 00:14:58,530
我知道应该早点道歉的
I know it should have come sooner.

250
00:14:58,530 --> 00:15:00,320
监督必须更严格
There needs to be more oversight.

251
00:15:00,330 --> 00:15:02,130
有美国国会监督呢
Well, there is congressional oversight.

252
00:15:02,130 --> 00:15:05,110
还有严格的制度来防止附带伤亡
We have a rigorous system to prevent collateral damage.

253
00:15:05,110 --> 00:15:07,860
平民被列为"其他激进分子"
Civilians are listed as "other militants."

254
00:15:08,010 --> 00:15:10,700
但政府并未提供确凿证据
But the government offers no evidence that's true.

255
00:15:11,260 --> 00:15:13,420
反正就我而言是没有
It definitely wasn't in my case.

256
00:15:14,250 --> 00:15:16,550
你们的程序哪里严格了
How rigorous can your process be?

257
00:15:17,340 --> 00:15:21,530
平民死于无人机袭击的数目
The numbers of non-combatants who are being killed by drone strikes

258
00:15:21,530 --> 00:15:22,730
比以往少多了
is lower than it's ever been.

259
00:15:22,730 --> 00:15:24,610
这些数字是假的
Those numbers are false.

260
00:15:24,610 --> 00:15:28,200
2010年只死了一个平民  肯定不对
One civilian killed in 2010? That has to be wrong.

261
00:15:28,200 --> 00:15:31,530
听着  我不认为五角大楼对此说了实话
Look, I don't think the Pentagon is being honest about--

262
00:15:36,620 --> 00:15:37,560
你没事吧
Are you okay?

263
00:15:39,270 --> 00:15:40,720
我去叫医生
I'll get the doctor up here.

264
00:15:41,510 --> 00:15:42,960
不必了  过一会儿就好
Don't do that. It'll pass.

265
00:15:44,740 --> 00:15:45,850
幻痛而已
Phantom pain.

266
00:15:54,950 --> 00:15:56,930
你知道我来时想做什么吗
You know what I dreamed of when I came here?

267
00:15:57,810 --> 00:16:00,300
徒手掐死你
Choking you with my bare hands.

268
00:16:12,350 --> 00:16:14,330
默罕默德先生  你可以恨我
Mr. Mahmoud, you may hate me.

269
00:16:14,970 --> 00:16:17,090
恨我的职位
You may hate the office I hold.

270
00:16:18,030 --> 00:16:19,530
但现实是
But here's the reality:

271
00:16:20,570 --> 00:16:25,340
每天我必须做出我但愿是正确的决定
I must make decisions every day that I hope are just.

272
00:16:25,660 --> 00:16:28,900
我也不能一直明辨是非
I don't know right from wrong all the time.

273
00:16:28,900 --> 00:16:30,360
我倒希望我能
I wish I did.

274
00:16:31,990 --> 00:16:34,430
但我决不能优柔寡断
But what I can't be is indecisive.

275
00:16:34,900 --> 00:16:39,150
《古兰经》中说  "夺一无辜之人性命
It says in the Qur'an: "The taking of one innocent life

276
00:16:39,880 --> 00:16:42,140
如了结全人类之性命"
is like the taking of all mankind."

277
00:16:43,100 --> 00:16:47,620
不过它也说  "救人一命
It also says that "The saving of one life

278
00:16:48,130 --> 00:16:50,970
如保全人类之命"
is like the saving of all mankind."

279
00:16:54,650 --> 00:16:56,670
你把我叫来  不是想跟我道歉
You didn't ask me here to apologize.

280
00:16:57,490 --> 00:16:59,080
而是想让我原谅你
You asked me here to forgive you.

281
00:17:01,720 --> 00:17:03,420
那袭击不是我下的命令
I didn't order the strike that--

282
00:17:05,080 --> 00:17:07,640
我不会原谅你  总统先生
I won't forgive you, Mr. President.

283
00:17:07,640 --> 00:17:10,370
我不想让你夜里能安心入睡
I don't want to make it any easier for you to sleep at night.

284
00:17:10,370 --> 00:17:14,110
知道《古兰经》的只字片语也不能免除你的罪孽
And knowing a few lines of the Qur'an does not absolve you.

285
00:17:19,390 --> 00:17:22,390
我对这个国家负有责任  默罕默德先生
I have a duty to this nation, Mr. Mahmoud.

286
00:17:22,390 --> 00:17:23,720
我发过誓的
I swore an oath.

287
00:17:23,720 --> 00:17:27,750
责任和谋杀之间有道微妙的界线
There's a fine line between duty and murder.

288
00:17:29,640 --> 00:17:33,150
只有你有能力阻止我遭遇的事
Only you have the power to stop what happened to me.

289
00:17:33,600 --> 00:17:37,910
下次你使用这份权力时  希望你能三思
The next time you wield it... I hope you'll think twice.

290
00:17:39,130 --> 00:17:41,360
一定会的  密查姆
Yes, of course. Meechum!

291
00:17:42,890 --> 00:17:43,660
先生  怎么了
Yes, sir?

292
00:17:43,980 --> 00:17:45,540
把默罕默德先生送出去
You show Mr. Mahmoud out.

293
00:17:50,870 --> 00:17:53,280
全国范围内持续两个月的随机抽样
Two months of random sampling across the country.

294
00:17:53,280 --> 00:17:56,130
不到所有可用数据的千分之一
Less than a tenth of a percent of all incoming data.

295
00:17:56,130 --> 00:17:56,930
怎么这么少
Why so little?

296
00:17:56,930 --> 00:17:58,970
你知道我们监视着多少个摄像机吗
You have any idea how many cameras we monitor?

297
00:17:58,970 --> 00:18:01,400
华盛顿所有主机的CPU核心份额
The CPU core quota of every mainframe in Washington

298
00:18:01,400 --> 00:18:02,990
都处理不了全部数据
couldn't handle all that data.

299
00:18:03,190 --> 00:18:05,410
我企图加倍样本范围但是触发了警报
I tried doubling the sample range and it set off alarms.

300
00:18:05,410 --> 00:18:07,270
我就差这么一点被抓
I came this fucking close to getting caught.

301
00:18:07,980 --> 00:18:09,890
我们只能缩小搜索范围
Okay, we just need to narrow the search, man.

302
00:18:10,550 --> 00:18:11,910
要覆盖的范围太广了
It's too much ground to cover.

303
00:18:12,690 --> 00:18:13,550
怎么缩小
How?

304
00:18:14,430 --> 00:18:16,750
我需要更多关于瑞秋的信息
I need more information on Rachel.

305
00:18:17,820 --> 00:18:20,820
她喜欢的书  电影之类的  什么都行
Favorite books, fuckin' movies. Anything.

306
00:18:21,770 --> 00:18:22,500
我一无所知
I don't know.

307
00:18:22,500 --> 00:18:24,490
拜托  她提起过去哪里吗
Come on. Did she ever talk about going anywhere?

308
00:18:24,490 --> 00:18:25,510
去什么地方旅游之类的
Traveling to some place?

309
00:18:25,520 --> 00:18:28,080
没有  她那时不能去旅游
No. Traveling wasn't an option.

310
00:18:28,900 --> 00:18:30,010
我需要更多信息
I need more, man.

311
00:18:32,460 --> 00:18:34,900
那另一个女孩丽萨呢
What about the other girl? Lisa.

312
00:18:34,900 --> 00:18:35,840
我正在看她的电子邮件
I'm reading her e-mails.

313
00:18:35,840 --> 00:18:37,690
并追踪了她的手机  什么也没发现
I'm tracking her phone. There's nothing there.

314
00:18:40,140 --> 00:18:41,910
但我们可以接近她  跟她谈谈
We should get close to her, though. We should talk to her.

315
00:18:41,910 --> 00:18:42,830
问出点有用的东西
Extract something.

316
00:18:42,830 --> 00:18:44,010
她会认出我来的
She might recognize me.

317
00:18:44,010 --> 00:18:44,920
我来吧
I'll do it.

318
00:18:46,400 --> 00:18:47,240
这叫我紧张
That makes me nervous.

319
00:18:47,250 --> 00:18:49,170
社会工程而已  我可以"黑"她的回忆
It's social engineering. I'll just hack her that way.

320
00:18:49,170 --> 00:18:50,610
她一点也不会起疑的
She won't suspect a thing.

321
00:18:53,310 --> 00:18:56,180
如果我们不试点新办法就找不到瑞秋
If we don't try something new, we're not gonna find Rachel.

322
00:19:01,720 --> 00:19:03,570
吃点煮花生吧
Help yourself to some boiled peanuts.

323
00:19:03,570 --> 00:19:05,960
不了  谢谢  盐太多了
No, thank you. Too much salt.

324
00:19:06,440 --> 00:19:07,490
我来这儿的第一周
First week I was here,

325
00:19:07,490 --> 00:19:10,000
我问服务员能不能给我来点煮花生
I asked one of the stewards if I could have some boiled peanuts.

326
00:19:10,000 --> 00:19:11,860
我小的时候经常吃
I used to eat them all the time as a kid,

327
00:19:11,900 --> 00:19:13,130
从那以后的每一天
and I'll be damned if there hasn't been

328
00:19:13,130 --> 00:19:15,510
我都要满满一碗的煮花生
a full bowl of peanuts here every day since.

329
00:19:15,510 --> 00:19:18,430
他们肯定有口昼夜不停煮花生的锅
They must have a pot boiling 'round the clock.

330
00:19:18,430 --> 00:19:20,770
露丝现在让我吃甘蓝脆片
Ruth has me eating kale crisps now.

331
00:19:20,770 --> 00:19:24,180
说对身体好  我受不了那东西
Says they're good for me. I can't stand the things.

332
00:19:24,190 --> 00:19:25,500
我让厨房给剥好了皮
I have them shucked in the kitchen,

333
00:19:25,500 --> 00:19:27,240
这样吃的时候不会弄脏手指
so you don't even have to get your fingers dirty.

334
00:19:27,250 --> 00:19:28,730
随意吃  享受一下生活
Feel free. Live a little.

335
00:19:33,660 --> 00:19:36,230
大法官先生  我们上次谈完后
Mr. Justice, since we last spoke,

336
00:19:36,230 --> 00:19:37,830
我做了很多反省
I've done a lot of soul searching.

337
00:19:38,770 --> 00:19:41,430
我要求你继续做法官  这不该
It was unfair of me to ask you to stay on the bench.

338
00:19:42,070 --> 00:19:44,670
如果你想退休  就可以退休
If you want to retire, you should.

339
00:19:45,560 --> 00:19:48,030
感谢您的考虑  总统先生
I appreciate your consideration, Mr. President.

340
00:19:48,030 --> 00:19:49,550
我认为我首先该做的
Well, I thought the first thing I should do

341
00:19:49,550 --> 00:19:51,850
就是找到一名合适的继任者
is to find a suitable successor.

342
00:19:51,850 --> 00:19:55,300
一个你会认可  能让你放心的人
Someone you would approve of to put your mind at ease,

343
00:19:55,640 --> 00:19:56,900
我想我找到了
and I think I've found one.

344
00:19:56,900 --> 00:19:57,760
是谁
Who?

345
00:19:57,760 --> 00:19:59,010
希瑟·邓巴
Heather Dunbar.

346
00:20:00,460 --> 00:20:02,450
我觉得她会是位很棒的法官
I think she'd be an excellent justice.

347
00:20:02,450 --> 00:20:03,850
很高兴你同意选她
I'm glad you agree.

348
00:20:03,850 --> 00:20:07,450
只是没想到会选她  毕竟她...
Just an unlikely choice, given how vociferous she--

349
00:20:07,450 --> 00:20:09,270
在沃克调查中咄咄逼人  是的
With the Walker investigation, yes.

350
00:20:09,270 --> 00:20:11,790
但那只会增加我对她的尊重
But that only increases my estimation of her.

351
00:20:11,900 --> 00:20:13,710
她很有责任感
She has a great sense of duty.

352
00:20:13,830 --> 00:20:16,740
比我共事过的任何副检察长都有责任心
More than any Solicitor General I've ever worked with.

353
00:20:17,570 --> 00:20:21,370
真希望我早能知道您找我来的原因
I wish I'd known the reason you invited me beforehand.

354
00:20:21,370 --> 00:20:23,090
就可以免去这趟麻烦了
I could have saved you the trouble.

355
00:20:23,140 --> 00:20:23,990
为什么呢
Why?

356
00:20:24,440 --> 00:20:26,480
我几个月前跟您聊过之后
After I talked to you a couple of months ago,

357
00:20:26,840 --> 00:20:28,780
露丝说您是给了我一份礼物
Ruth said you'd given me a gift.

358
00:20:28,930 --> 00:20:32,070
如果我不当法官  会很痛苦
That I would be miserable if I weren't on the bench.

359
00:20:32,070 --> 00:20:35,540
她跟我儿子都谈了  他们也同意
She talked to my sons and they all agreed.

360
00:20:35,540 --> 00:20:37,430
只要我的健康还允许
As long as I'm well enough to serve the court,

361
00:20:37,430 --> 00:20:38,890
我就想继续做下去
that's where I want to be.

362
00:20:40,130 --> 00:20:42,240
我们留意着点2016的走势
And we'll keep an eye on 2016.

363
00:20:42,240 --> 00:20:46,740
如果共和党看上去能赢  我就辞职
If it looks as though the Republicans will win, I'll step down.

364
00:20:46,740 --> 00:20:49,890
如果不会  我就留下  但不用着急
If not, I'll stay. But, there's no rush.

365
00:20:55,450 --> 00:20:57,320
我非得毁掉这个人吗
Must I destroy this man?

366
00:20:58,040 --> 00:20:59,140
总统先生
Mr. President?

367
00:21:03,720 --> 00:21:06,640
不  我不想
No. I won't.

368
00:21:06,940 --> 00:21:07,840
您说什么
Excuse me?

369
00:21:11,550 --> 00:21:14,170
我不能袖手旁观
I won't stand by

370
00:21:14,860 --> 00:21:17,280
看你做这个错误的决定
and watch you make this mistake.

371
00:21:19,130 --> 00:21:21,090
我已经考虑好了
I've thought this through.

372
00:21:22,660 --> 00:21:24,210
我们不是朋友  罗伯特
We're not friends, Robert.

373
00:21:24,210 --> 00:21:26,770
我们没那么熟
We don't know each other that well.

374
00:21:26,830 --> 00:21:28,270
但我关心你
But I care about you.

375
00:21:28,780 --> 00:21:32,080
因为你在法院服务了超过20年
Because you served for more than 20 years on the bench.

376
00:21:32,080 --> 00:21:34,910
你裁定的判例存世会比你我都长久
You've established legal precedents that will outlive both of us.

377
00:21:34,910 --> 00:21:35,820
而且...
And...

378
00:21:35,820 --> 00:21:39,110
昨天的事你也许可以用人老糊涂解释过去
maybe you can explain away yesterday as a senior moment.

379
00:21:39,110 --> 00:21:42,310
但要是再出现你没法解释的其他状况呢
But what if another moment happens that you can't explain away?

380
00:21:42,310 --> 00:21:45,860
万一你患病的消息泄露出去了呢
What if somehow the news of your illness leaks?

381
00:21:45,880 --> 00:21:49,390
那你写下的每个判决都会受人怀疑
Then every decision you've written will be called into question.

382
00:21:49,390 --> 00:21:50,590
都将受到质疑
They'll be challenged.

383
00:21:50,590 --> 00:21:54,090
你一生的成果瞬间就会化为乌有
And a life's work will be undone in a heartbeat.

384
00:21:54,130 --> 00:21:57,110
您有什么其他心思吗
Do you have some ulterior motive here?

385
00:21:57,130 --> 00:21:59,270
只是为你着想
Only your best interests.

386
00:21:59,690 --> 00:22:01,120
那为什么要这么急
But why the urgency?

387
00:22:04,300 --> 00:22:05,850
我想保护你
I want to protect you.

388
00:22:07,220 --> 00:22:10,850
大法官  我在请求你  在恳求你
Justice, I'm asking you, I'm pleading with you.

389
00:22:11,770 --> 00:22:15,340
别让事情脱离你的掌控
Don't let events get out of your control.

390
00:22:16,030 --> 00:22:17,410
你能重新考虑吗
Will you reconsider?

391
00:22:19,800 --> 00:22:22,170
谢谢您的关心  总统先生
I appreciate your concern, Mr. President.

392
00:22:23,190 --> 00:22:26,630
我再跟露丝商量一下  给您答复
Let me speak again to Ruth and I'll get back to you.

393
00:22:27,440 --> 00:22:28,760
谢谢你  大法官
Thank you, Justice.

394
00:22:29,190 --> 00:22:30,380
你这是禁言
It's a moratorium.

395
00:22:30,570 --> 00:22:31,730
我们不那么叫
We're not calling it that.

396
00:22:31,730 --> 00:22:33,620
随你们叫什么  但没人开口
Call it whatever you want, nobody's talking.

397
00:22:33,880 --> 00:22:35,580
我们在避免发布错误信息
We're trying to prevent misinformation.

398
00:22:35,580 --> 00:22:37,500
我本想写《美就法》的报道
I'm supposed to write about AmWorks.

399
00:22:37,500 --> 00:22:38,570
但行政部门都
How can I do that  when no one

400
00:22:38,570 --> 00:22:40,590
没人跟我说话我该怎么写
from the executive branch will speak to me?

401
00:22:40,590 --> 00:22:42,530
国会那边情况瞬息万变
This thing's shifting under our feet in Congress.

402
00:22:42,530 --> 00:22:45,110
等我写完早简报  已经成了昨日黄花
By the time I finish the morning brief, it's already outdated.

403
00:22:45,110 --> 00:22:47,770
我不是要求跟总统一对一对话  但...
I'm not asking for a one-on-one with the president, but...

404
00:22:48,020 --> 00:22:49,680
但劳工部长  财政部长
the Secretary of Labor, Treasury,

405
00:22:49,680 --> 00:22:51,030
他的哪个经济顾问都行
one of his economic advisors.

406
00:22:51,040 --> 00:22:52,560
给你特殊待遇吗
Give you special treatment?

407
00:22:53,390 --> 00:22:55,730
我觉得你们下令禁言是因为你们要输
I think you issued the moratorium because you're losing the battle.

408
00:22:55,730 --> 00:22:57,720
事关五千亿美金
It's 500 billion dollars.

409
00:22:57,840 --> 00:23:00,100
这是罗斯福新政以来最大的就业计划
This is the largest jobs program since the New Deal.

410
00:23:00,110 --> 00:23:03,040
当然是场激战  但那不代表我们失利
Of course it's a slugfest. That doesn't mean we're losing.

411
00:23:03,280 --> 00:23:05,430
那让我跟能确证那点的人谈谈
Then let me speak to someone who can confirm that.

412
00:23:05,680 --> 00:23:07,870
因为我从共和党人那里听到的
Because all I'm hearing from the Republicans is that

413
00:23:07,870 --> 00:23:09,480
都是《美就法》绝对不会通过
AmWorks will never see the light of day.

414
00:23:09,480 --> 00:23:10,830
我很同情你  艾拉
I sympathize with you, Ayla.

415
00:23:10,830 --> 00:23:12,780
我也希望能让你如愿
I wish I could give you what you want.

416
00:23:14,370 --> 00:23:15,410
总统要我们过去
The president needs us.

417
00:23:16,170 --> 00:23:17,240
我们迟点再聊
So we'll talk later.

418
00:23:18,880 --> 00:23:21,430
迈克尔·科里根  上周国宴时
Michael Corrigan, the activist who organized the protest

419
00:23:21,430 --> 00:23:22,920
组织抗议的激进分子
at the state dinner last month,

420
00:23:22,920 --> 00:23:25,500
三小时前在莫斯科被俄国警方逮捕
arrested by Russian police three hours ago in Moscow.

421
00:23:25,980 --> 00:23:27,260
视频已经疯传
The video is going viral.

422
00:23:27,900 --> 00:23:32,630
他是国内外知名的同性恋权利活动家
He's a high profile gay rights activist, nationally and abroad.

423
00:23:32,930 --> 00:23:36,090
过去六周以来他一直在俄罗斯高调活动
And he's been very vocal in Russia over the last six weeks.

424
00:23:36,130 --> 00:23:37,800
这是联调局关于他的档案  先生
Here's the bureau file on him, sir.

425
00:23:37,920 --> 00:23:39,610
我们跟克里姆林宫接触了吗
Have we been in touch with the Kremlin?

426
00:23:39,620 --> 00:23:42,070
杜兰特国务卿现在正在丹吉尔[摩洛哥城市]
Secretary Durant is in Tangier right now.

427
00:23:42,070 --> 00:23:44,990
我打电话知会了她  她也联系了布加耶夫
I briefed her by phone and she reached out to Bugayev.

428
00:23:44,990 --> 00:23:46,890
但他们还没有联系上
But they have not connected yet.

429
00:23:46,920 --> 00:23:49,410
格莱姆斯大使也在莫斯科上下疏通
Ambassador Grimes is making calls in Moscow,

430
00:23:49,410 --> 00:23:50,440
但目前没有进展
but nobody's engaging,

431
00:23:50,440 --> 00:23:53,400
只知道他们打算提出严重的指控
other than to say they plan on fully prosecuting him.

432
00:23:54,110 --> 00:23:55,880
大使  你认为这会不会是对你在联合国
Ambassador, do you think this could be in retaliation

433
00:23:55,880 --> 00:23:57,460
活动的报复行为
for what you're doing at the UN?

434
00:23:57,550 --> 00:23:58,610
有这个可能
It could be.

435
00:23:59,020 --> 00:24:01,790
俄罗斯人对这个决议案非常不满
The Russians are very upset about this resolution.

436
00:24:02,020 --> 00:24:04,000
我去莫里科夫那里探探口风
I'll see what I can find out from Moryakov.

437
00:24:04,810 --> 00:24:06,850
把新闻发布会推迟到明天
Let's hold off on the press conference until tomorrow.

438
00:24:06,850 --> 00:24:09,030
我希望能汇报些好消息  而不是两手空空
I'd like to deliver some good news instead of no news.

439
00:24:09,030 --> 00:24:09,860
同时
In the meantime,

440
00:24:09,910 --> 00:24:12,300
发一个声明  说我们正在接触莫斯科方面
put out a statement that we're in communication with Moscow.

441
00:24:12,300 --> 00:24:14,150
我们正竭尽所能
And that we're doing everything we can

442
00:24:14,150 --> 00:24:16,170
把科里根先生营救回美国  谢谢各位
to get Mr. Corrigan back to the United States. Thank you all.

443
00:24:18,080 --> 00:24:19,360
我个人也讨厌这套法律
Personally, I hate the law.

444
00:24:19,360 --> 00:24:21,470
古板又恐同的玩意
It's medieval homophobic nonsense.

445
00:24:21,470 --> 00:24:22,620
但法律就是法律
But it's the law.

446
00:24:22,700 --> 00:24:23,900
我们刚刚谈过
I don't think it's coincidence

447
00:24:23,900 --> 00:24:26,220
科里根就被逮捕了  我不觉得是巧合
that Corrigan was arrested after our conversation.

448
00:24:26,220 --> 00:24:28,140
我也不觉得是巧合
Well, I wouldn't think it was a coincidence either.

449
00:24:28,140 --> 00:24:30,020
那你有什么期望
So what do you hope to achieve?

450
00:24:30,020 --> 00:24:32,140
我的期望和你一样  让科里根先生获释
The same thing as you do: Mr. Corrigan's release.

451
00:24:32,140 --> 00:24:33,870
前提是我撤回决议案
If I withdraw the resolution.

452
00:24:33,870 --> 00:24:36,720
我认为莫斯科肯定会将此举视为善意的表示
I think Moscow would certainly see it as a sign of goodwill.

453
00:24:37,210 --> 00:24:38,750
我们可不会为了表示善意
Well, we don't barter goodwill

454
00:24:38,750 --> 00:24:40,300
就拿美国公民的自由做交易
for the freedom of American citizens.

455
00:24:40,300 --> 00:24:43,490
我提议过将他立即驱逐出境
I actually advocated for his immediate deportation.

456
00:24:43,490 --> 00:24:45,690
我也认为把他扔进大牢只能适得其反
I agree that tossing him in jail is counterproductive,

457
00:24:45,690 --> 00:24:47,520
但高层心意已决
but my superiors are adamant.

458
00:24:47,650 --> 00:24:50,130
帮佩特罗夫看清局势吧
Save Petrov from himself.

459
00:24:50,670 --> 00:24:52,420
我可没资格质疑他
It's not my place to question him.

460
00:24:52,420 --> 00:24:54,330
和你不同  我毕竟没嫁给总统
Unlike you, I'm not married to my boss.

461
00:24:57,620 --> 00:25:00,850
我会把克里姆林宫的立场转达给总统
I'll relay the Kremlin's position to the president.

462
00:25:04,580 --> 00:25:06,900
如果我们让步  约旦河谷计划就搁浅了
If we give in, the Jordan Valley plan is over

463
00:25:06,900 --> 00:25:09,680
还让俄罗斯人觉得他们可以漫天要价
and we show the Russians we can be blackmailed.

464
00:25:09,680 --> 00:25:11,970
难道我们眼睁睁让科里根坐穿牢底吗
So we're just supposed to let Corrigan rot away?

465
00:25:12,020 --> 00:25:14,320
我想如果我们在联合国保持强硬立场
I think if we continue to drive hard at the UN,

466
00:25:14,320 --> 00:25:15,560
我们就会有更多筹码
we'll gain leverage.

467
00:25:15,580 --> 00:25:16,850
凯茜怎么想
What does Cathy think?

468
00:25:16,850 --> 00:25:17,520
她也同意
She agrees.

469
00:25:17,520 --> 00:25:20,690
只要科里根一天没放出来  我就得挨一天骂
I'm gonna take flak every day that Corrigan remains in jail.

470
00:25:20,690 --> 00:25:22,430
如果你退步的话就会被骂死
And you'll take more if you back down.

471
00:25:22,430 --> 00:25:24,200
但这样一来我就得在新闻发布会上
But it does mean I have to get in front of the press

472
00:25:24,200 --> 00:25:26,390
两手空空地面对媒体
with absolutely nothing of substance to say.

473
00:25:26,400 --> 00:25:28,760
你在国会混了20年  没话找话你最拿手
You spent 20 years in Congress. You're good at that.

474
00:25:31,750 --> 00:25:33,030
听到你笑真好
It's good to hear you laugh.

475
00:25:34,270 --> 00:25:36,230
睡一会儿吧  我明天再打给你
Get some sleep. I'll call you tomorrow.

476
00:25:36,430 --> 00:25:37,170
晚安
Good night.

477
00:25:40,660 --> 00:25:43,540
具体是谁负责华盛顿和莫斯科之间的沟通
Who specifically is communicating between Washington and Moscow?

478
00:25:43,540 --> 00:25:45,650
两国之间的联络是由国务院
All of our communication is between the State Department

479
00:25:45,650 --> 00:25:48,040
和俄罗斯外交部负责的  艾拉
and the Russian Foreign Ministry. Ayla.

480
00:25:48,160 --> 00:25:50,990
您在声明中一直称这是侵犯言论自由
In your statement, you persisted in calling this a free speech issue,

481
00:25:50,990 --> 00:25:53,280
但同性恋权利难道不也是主题吗
but isn't gay rights really at the center of this?

482
00:25:53,570 --> 00:25:56,610
科里根先生是因为自由发表意见被捕的
Well, Mr. Corrigan was arrested for speaking his mind.

483
00:25:56,630 --> 00:25:57,400
无论他是持什么立场
No matter what his opinions...

484
00:25:57,400 --> 00:25:58,700
您是不是在回避问题  总统先生
Aren't you skirting that, Mr. President,

485
00:25:58,700 --> 00:26:00,850
因为您在同性恋权利问题上立场含混不清
because your stance on gay rights is unclear?

486
00:26:03,590 --> 00:26:06,750
现在清楚无疑的是科里根先生的被捕不公正
What is clear is that Mr. Corrigan's detainment is unjust

487
00:26:06,750 --> 00:26:08,880
而如我所言  我们正动用一切手段
and, as I said, we're doing everything we can

488
00:26:08,910 --> 00:26:10,670
确保他安全回家  扎克利
to make sure that he can come home. Yes, Zachary.

489
00:26:10,670 --> 00:26:11,430
我还没问完
Following up.

490
00:26:11,430 --> 00:26:13,000
如果您不参选  那么回避同性恋问题
Isn't dodging gay rights a calculated move

491
00:26:13,000 --> 00:26:14,830
是不是太过算计了
for a man not running for office?

492
00:26:16,380 --> 00:26:17,620
你说我在回避问题
You think I'm dodging?

493
00:26:18,400 --> 00:26:20,890
那我今天就把话跟你说清楚
Well, then let me be as clear as I possibly can be.

494
00:26:21,210 --> 00:26:22,840
同性恋群体是有权利的
Gay people have rights.

495
00:26:23,050 --> 00:26:24,880
而本届政府始终坚信
And this administration has always believed

496
00:26:24,880 --> 00:26:27,210
科里根先生有权就任何问题
that Mr. Corrigan has the right to speak his mind

497
00:26:27,380 --> 00:26:29,740
自由表达观点  而无需担心被捕
without fear of being arrested on any issue,

498
00:26:29,740 --> 00:26:31,940
不管是同性恋权利还是别的什么
whether it's gay rights or something else.

499
00:26:32,090 --> 00:26:33,240
另一件清楚无疑的事
And what is also quite clear

500
00:26:33,240 --> 00:26:35,360
就是你在礼仪课上肯定没好好听讲
is that you must have failed etiquette class.

501
00:26:35,890 --> 00:26:36,610
扎克利
Yes, Zachary.

502
00:26:36,610 --> 00:26:38,210
-总统先生  -您为什么不接见约翰·帕斯特纳克
- Mr. Prisident-- - Why won't you speak to John Pasternak,

503
00:26:38,210 --> 00:26:38,870
-迈克尔·科里根的丈夫  -萨伊德女士
- Michael Corrigan's husband? - Ms. Sayyad,

504
00:26:38,870 --> 00:26:40,610
今天到场的还有其他记者和媒体
there are other members of the press here today,

505
00:26:40,610 --> 00:26:42,260
帕斯特纳克先生一直在试图联系白宫
Mr. Pasternak has been trying to contact the White House

506
00:26:42,260 --> 00:26:43,450
但却没人理他
and no one will speak with him.

507
00:26:43,460 --> 00:26:44,770
实在抱歉各位  我还有会
I do apologize, I have a meeting.

508
00:26:44,770 --> 00:26:46,410
真希望能回答你们所有人的问题
I wish I could've gotten to all your questions.

509
00:26:46,410 --> 00:26:47,830
还有任何疑问的话
But if you have any further inquiries,

510
00:26:47,830 --> 00:26:49,960
请问格雷森先生  非常感谢
please direct them to Mr. Grayson. Thank you very much.

511
00:26:51,130 --> 00:26:52,220
抱歉  先生
I apologize, sir.

512
00:26:55,230 --> 00:26:56,070
你太过分了
You went too far.

513
00:26:56,070 --> 00:26:57,170
那是我的工作
I did my job.

514
00:26:57,390 --> 00:26:59,730
这是有规则的  要顾及礼仪
There's protocol. There's basic decorum.

515
00:26:59,740 --> 00:27:02,760
那这样  你为我解除《美就法》的禁言
How about this: you lift the moratorium for me on AmWorks,

516
00:27:02,820 --> 00:27:05,470
我消失五周  专心酝酿长文
I disappear for five weeks. Focus on my long-lead piece.

517
00:27:05,470 --> 00:27:06,960
科里根和其他事我都不碰
I don't touch Corrigan or anything else.

518
00:27:06,960 --> 00:27:08,610
你就指望我来警告你
You wanted me to chew you out.

519
00:27:09,010 --> 00:27:10,710
如果能让你开口的话
If that's what it takes to get us talking.

520
00:27:10,710 --> 00:27:12,780
所以我要收回你的白宫记者证
Which is why I need your credential.

521
00:27:13,920 --> 00:27:15,540
-什么  -你的白宫记者证
- What? - Your credential.

522
00:27:17,670 --> 00:27:19,320
-你开玩笑吧  -我笑了吗
- You're kidding. - Do you see me laughing?

523
00:27:20,310 --> 00:27:21,570
你无权收回我的白宫记者证
You don't control my credential.

524
00:27:21,570 --> 00:27:23,360
白宫记者协会才有权
The Correspondents' Association does.

525
00:27:23,360 --> 00:27:25,000
我刚跟乔尔·维曼聊过
And I just spoke to Joel Weinmann.

526
00:27:26,200 --> 00:27:27,140
他不会的
He wouldn't.

527
00:27:27,570 --> 00:27:28,850
你成功了  艾拉
You succeeded, Ayla.

528
00:27:29,360 --> 00:27:30,820
我要为所有
I'm lifting the moratorium

529
00:27:31,230 --> 00:27:33,230
其他记者解除《美就法》的禁言
for every other member of the press corps.

530
00:27:33,410 --> 00:27:34,830
代价是你的白宫记者证
The price was your credential.

531
00:27:36,540 --> 00:27:38,060
他没有理由
He has no grounds.

532
00:27:38,300 --> 00:27:39,870
你对总统不敬
You disrespected the president,

533
00:27:40,500 --> 00:27:43,360
对政府不敬  更对你的同行们不敬
the office, and most importantly, your fellow colleagues.

534
00:27:43,770 --> 00:27:44,940
根本不难说服他
It wasn't a tough sell.

535
00:27:44,940 --> 00:27:46,500
那我下一篇报道就写这个
Then this becomes my next story.

536
00:27:46,500 --> 00:27:48,960
迫害记者  上下勾结  尽职却付出代价
Punishing a member of the press. Collusion. Pay for play.

537
00:27:48,970 --> 00:27:49,970
我会否认
And I'll deny.

538
00:27:50,780 --> 00:27:52,740
而且你觉得记者协会主席
And do you think the head of the association

539
00:27:52,910 --> 00:27:54,150
会承认吗
is gonna admit anything?

540
00:27:54,820 --> 00:27:58,100
艾拉  你两边都没有盟友了
You don't have any friends, Ayla, on either side of the fence.

541
00:27:58,110 --> 00:28:00,380
总统刚就言论自由发表了声明
The president just made a statement about free speech.

542
00:28:00,380 --> 00:28:02,650
你就要把记者踢出白宫吗
Now you're gonna start kicking reporters out of the White House?

543
00:28:02,770 --> 00:28:05,550
-不  只踢你  -不只是我
- No. Just you. - No, not just me!

544
00:28:06,280 --> 00:28:08,420
你惹上了全美第二大日报
You're fucking with the second largest daily in America.

545
00:28:08,420 --> 00:28:09,020
你能甩掉我
You can get rid of me,

546
00:28:09,020 --> 00:28:11,290
但甩不掉我工作的报社
but you can't get rid of the institution I work for.

547
00:28:13,680 --> 00:28:14,530
说完了吗
You done?

548
00:28:15,950 --> 00:28:18,650
别一时得权就昏了头  赛斯
Don't let your 15 minutes of power go to your head, Seth.

549
00:28:20,600 --> 00:28:24,370
封壳你留着做纪念吧
You can keep the plastic if you want... as a souvenir.

550
00:28:25,160 --> 00:28:26,570
反正也只能作纪念了
That's all it's good for, now.

551
00:28:36,530 --> 00:28:37,240
你好
Hello?

552
00:28:38,470 --> 00:28:39,090
嗯
Yeah.

553
00:28:43,710 --> 00:28:44,770
真的吗
Are you serious?

554
00:28:49,410 --> 00:28:50,390
好吧
Okay.

555
00:28:51,720 --> 00:28:52,560
操
Fuck.

556
00:28:56,240 --> 00:28:57,660
我有事找总统
I need to speak to the president.

557
00:28:59,570 --> 00:29:04,140
我们希望通过法律完善政府
Through our laws, we seek to create a more perfect union.

558
00:29:04,540 --> 00:29:06,590
滥用法律的政府官员
Government officials who abuse the law,

559
00:29:07,050 --> 00:29:08,170
或者哪怕是
or, at the very least,

560
00:29:08,170 --> 00:29:11,170
打法律的擦边球  借机牟利的人
exploit the edges of it for their own personal gain,

561
00:29:11,750 --> 00:29:16,540
都是在玷污民主  削弱这个伟大的国家
tarnish our democracy and weaken the bonds of our great nation.

562
00:29:17,230 --> 00:29:21,040
民主党必须走出丑闻的阴影
The Democratic Party must step out of the shadow of scandal

563
00:29:21,150 --> 00:29:22,810
改头换面
and redefine itself.

564
00:29:22,810 --> 00:29:24,650
她演完了让她来一趟
I want her here when she's done with this stunt.

565
00:29:24,650 --> 00:29:29,680
迎接一个透明  真诚  正义的新时代
Embracing a new era of transparency, honesty and justice,

566
00:29:25,300 --> 00:29:29,560
{\pos(38.7,189)}{\an7}希瑟·邓巴
最高法院门外

567
00:29:29,950 --> 00:29:33,880
这个国家需要一位曾在全美诸多法庭里
this country deserves a president who has dedicated herself

568
00:29:33,880 --> 00:29:37,320
为这个理想献身的总统
to those ideals in this court and many others,

569
00:29:37,910 --> 00:29:41,030
一位毕生都在捍卫法律的总统
who has spent her entire life defending the law,

570
00:29:41,430 --> 00:29:44,810
一位如今想投入法律执行的总统
and who now wants to dedicate herself to enforcing it.

571
00:29:45,710 --> 00:29:48,620
迎接一位正直的总统吧
Let's restore integrity to the Oval Office.

572
00:29:48,830 --> 00:29:53,390
用总统的权力根除腐败  以身作则
Use its power to root out corruption and lead by example.

573
00:29:53,750 --> 00:29:56,850
今天  在家人和朋友面前
Today, before my family and friends,

574
00:29:57,120 --> 00:30:00,930
在上帝和美国最高法院面前
my God, and the highest court in our land,

575
00:30:01,450 --> 00:30:02,840
我宣布参选
I announce my candidacy

576
00:30:02,840 --> 00:30:05,980
美利坚合众国总统
for President of the United States of America.

577
00:30:06,390 --> 00:30:08,180
邓巴女士此次宣布参选
There was no indication Ms. Dunbar

578
00:30:08,180 --> 00:30:10,140
并没有任何先兆
had plans to run for president.

579
00:30:10,170 --> 00:30:12,160
她将成为史上第二位
This will make her the second Solicitor General

580
00:30:12,160 --> 00:30:13,870
参选总统的副检察长
in history to run for president,

581
00:30:13,870 --> 00:30:16,880
另一位是1908年的威廉·霍华德·塔夫特
the only other being William Howard Taft in 1908.

582
00:30:17,270 --> 00:30:19,410
安德伍德总统已经宣布不会...
With President Underwood declaring he will not--

583
00:30:21,470 --> 00:30:23,310
-总统先生  -邓巴女士
- Mr. President. - Ms. Dunbar.

584
00:30:24,470 --> 00:30:26,220
请坐吧
Please, take a seat.

585
00:30:28,080 --> 00:30:29,240
我的辞呈
My letter of resignation.

586
00:30:29,240 --> 00:30:30,600
我不能接受
I can't accept that.

587
00:30:30,720 --> 00:30:31,920
你对我们太重要了
You're too valuable to us.

588
00:30:31,920 --> 00:30:34,350
我要竞选就得离职
I can't run for office as Solicitor General.

589
00:30:34,350 --> 00:30:36,050
那你该重新考虑下竞选的事
Then you should reconsider running for office.

590
00:30:36,060 --> 00:30:37,560
现在已经太迟了
It's too late for that, I think.

591
00:30:37,570 --> 00:30:38,970
我不理解  希瑟
I don't understand, Heather.

592
00:30:38,970 --> 00:30:41,920
我给了你最高法院的位置
I offered you a seat on the Supreme Court.

593
00:30:41,930 --> 00:30:44,440
前提是雅各布斯辞职  但他不会
If Jacobs was stepping down, which he isn't.

594
00:30:45,420 --> 00:30:46,310
你跟他谈过
You spoke to him.

595
00:30:46,310 --> 00:30:49,170
作为副检察长  我跟每位法官关系都很好
As Solicitor General, I'm friendly with all the justices.

596
00:30:49,390 --> 00:30:50,970
我没有声张那些关系
I keep those relationships private

597
00:30:50,970 --> 00:30:53,640
免得人怀疑法官对我有偏袒
so no one will suspect any bias toward me.

598
00:30:54,080 --> 00:30:56,320
但罗伯特跟我关系很好
But Robert and I are very close.

599
00:30:56,600 --> 00:30:58,950
他和露丝每月都邀我去吃顿晚饭
He and Ruth have me over for dinner once a month.

600
00:30:59,150 --> 00:31:01,300
所以你早知道他患病的事了
So you already knew about the Alzheimer's?

601
00:31:01,300 --> 00:31:03,230
确诊当天他就告诉我了
He told me the day he was diagnosed.

602
00:31:03,230 --> 00:31:05,930
我一向是为他的利益考虑
I've never had anything but his best interests at heart.

603
00:31:05,930 --> 00:31:08,400
你并不关心罗伯特
You don't care about Robert.

604
00:31:08,430 --> 00:31:10,490
你只是想让我出局
You wanted to sideline me.

605
00:31:10,730 --> 00:31:15,240
那么你真觉得你有机会进这间办公室
So you actually think you have a shot at this office?

606
00:31:15,240 --> 00:31:17,950
是的  党内领导层也这么觉得
Yes, I do. And so does the leadership.

607
00:31:18,850 --> 00:31:19,970
你是不自量力  希瑟
You're in over your head, Heather,

608
00:31:19,970 --> 00:31:22,480
无论博奇和乌麦克跟你说了什么
no matter what Birch and Womack are telling you.

609
00:31:23,190 --> 00:31:25,210
你在乎什么呢  总统先生
Why should it concern you, Mr. President?

610
00:31:25,500 --> 00:31:27,030
你已经宣布不参加竞选了
You've announced that you're not running.

611
00:31:27,030 --> 00:31:28,810
你参选有个人感情因素吗
Is this personal for you?

612
00:31:29,960 --> 00:31:31,150
别自作多情了
Don't flatter yourself.

613
00:31:31,150 --> 00:31:33,340
你整倒了沃克  但你打不倒我
You got Walker, but you couldn't get me.

614
00:31:33,340 --> 00:31:35,250
我没必要通过竞选来把你赶走
I don't have to run to make sure you leave office.

615
00:31:35,250 --> 00:31:36,480
你本来就赢不了
You couldn't win anyway.

616
00:31:36,500 --> 00:31:38,980
我参选是因为我知道我能做个好总统
I'm running because I know I'd make a good president.

617
00:31:38,980 --> 00:31:41,290
你很可能能当个好总统
You might very well make a good president.

618
00:31:42,250 --> 00:31:44,400
但现在  你是在妄想
But right now, you're being delusional.

619
00:31:44,400 --> 00:31:46,630
博奇来找我时  我还不确定
When Birch approached me, I wasn't sure.

620
00:31:47,730 --> 00:31:50,090
我很动心  但也知道成功机会不大
I was tempted, but I knew it was a long shot.

621
00:31:50,600 --> 00:31:53,350
你给我提名时  我完全不知所措了
And when you offered the nomination, I was overwhelmed.

622
00:31:53,350 --> 00:31:55,560
那是我毕生工作的目标
It's what I'd been working toward my entire career.

623
00:31:56,130 --> 00:31:57,400
但后来我跟罗伯特聊了聊
But then I spoke to Robert.

624
00:31:57,400 --> 00:31:59,310
他告诉我你是怎么威胁他后
And when he told me how you threatened him,

625
00:31:59,310 --> 00:32:00,900
我就知道我必须参选
I knew I had to run.

626
00:32:00,900 --> 00:32:03,950
总得有人把这个办公室里的臭气洗洗干净
Someone needs to scrub the stink from this office.

627
00:32:03,950 --> 00:32:05,290
我没有威胁他
I didn't threaten him.

628
00:32:05,290 --> 00:32:06,090
那你管那叫什么
What would you call it?

629
00:32:06,090 --> 00:32:07,890
我是想挽救他
I was trying to save him,

630
00:32:07,890 --> 00:32:10,260
就像我现在也是想挽救你
in the same way I'm trying to save you now.

631
00:32:10,370 --> 00:32:13,310
一旦他患病的消息泄露  这总会泄露的
Once the news of his Alzheimer's gets out, which it will,

632
00:32:13,310 --> 00:32:15,580
因为无论我们怎么说谎隐瞒
because no matter how much we all try to lie about it,

633
00:32:15,580 --> 00:32:16,720
它总会传出去
it's gonna leak,

634
00:32:16,720 --> 00:32:19,640
你能想象那对他的名誉会造成多大影响吗
can you imagine what that's going to do to his reputation?

635
00:32:19,640 --> 00:32:21,080
他不该遭此境遇
He deserves better than that.

636
00:32:21,080 --> 00:32:23,720
你也该得到比陪跑更高的地位
And you deserve better than being an also-ran.

637
00:32:23,760 --> 00:32:26,190
帮我说服他
Help me convince him.

638
00:32:26,420 --> 00:32:30,080
接受最高法院你应得的那个职位
Take the seat on the court where you belong.

639
00:32:30,410 --> 00:32:32,600
你就是这么说服自己的吗
Is this how you live with yourself?

640
00:32:33,580 --> 00:32:37,150
把不堪的目的说成好听的
By rationalizing the obscene into the palatable?

641
00:32:42,070 --> 00:32:43,720
我还没允许你走
I haven't excused you yet.

642
00:32:43,720 --> 00:32:44,950
爱荷华初选见吧
See you in Iowa.

643
00:33:09,980 --> 00:33:11,060
没有信仰
I wouldn't have made it

644
00:33:11,060 --> 00:33:14,260
我是支撑不过这八个月的
through the past eight months without my faith.

645
00:33:15,720 --> 00:33:18,580
但没有这个团体  我也支撑不过来
But I wouldn't have made it without this community, either.

646
00:33:19,980 --> 00:33:21,370
在那些艰难的日子里...
And on tough days...

647
00:33:22,890 --> 00:33:24,450
我一直提醒自己这点
I remind myself of that.

648
00:33:25,490 --> 00:33:26,670
我不是一个人
That I'm not alone.

649
00:33:28,190 --> 00:33:29,840
我有你们大家
That I have all of you.

650
00:33:31,440 --> 00:33:34,750
我认为承认这点是很重要的
And I think it's important to acknowledge that.

651
00:33:35,690 --> 00:33:37,020
还有表达感谢
To give thanks.

652
00:33:38,170 --> 00:33:39,370
所以  谢谢你们
So thank you.

653
00:33:40,420 --> 00:33:41,500
谢谢所有人
All of you.

654
00:33:41,960 --> 00:33:46,280
谢谢你们一直都在我身边  在我心里
For always being there. For always being here.

655
00:33:51,460 --> 00:33:53,170
我得走了  再见
I have to go. I'll see you soon.

656
00:33:59,720 --> 00:34:01,760
我只想说一句  你刚才讲的...
I just wanted to say, what you said...

657
00:34:02,180 --> 00:34:04,370
真的让我很受触动  关于团体的
it really connected with me. About community.

658
00:34:04,370 --> 00:34:05,220
-谢谢  -嗯
- Thank you. - Yeah.

659
00:34:05,220 --> 00:34:06,100
我很高兴
I'm glad.

660
00:34:06,260 --> 00:34:06,810
我叫丽萨
I'm Lisa.

661
00:34:06,810 --> 00:34:08,070
我叫麦克斯
Of course. Max.

662
00:34:08,910 --> 00:34:09,550
你是新来的
You're new.

663
00:34:09,550 --> 00:34:11,020
其实是第一次来
It was my first time, actually.

664
00:34:11,020 --> 00:34:12,190
你在附近住吗
Do you live around here?

665
00:34:12,190 --> 00:34:13,910
住陶森市  开车来的
Towson. Just drove up.

666
00:34:14,980 --> 00:34:16,370
你怎么找到我们的
How did you find out about us?

667
00:34:16,600 --> 00:34:17,360
网上
Online.

668
00:34:19,020 --> 00:34:19,880
网站
Website.

669
00:34:20,690 --> 00:34:22,550
我就是到处看看
Yeah, I was surfing around, and I was...

670
00:34:22,660 --> 00:34:24,680
在找点东西
I was looking for something and...

671
00:34:25,910 --> 00:34:27,360
-太傻了  -不会的
- It's stupid. - No. No, no.

672
00:34:27,700 --> 00:34:28,600
告诉我吧
Tell me.

673
00:34:31,500 --> 00:34:34,370
好吧  几个月前  一个姑娘
Okay, well, a few months ago, this girl...

674
00:34:36,670 --> 00:34:38,940
其实是我一生挚爱...
the love of my life, actually...

675
00:34:40,070 --> 00:34:40,910
分手了吗
Breakup?

676
00:34:41,530 --> 00:34:42,960
她离开了我
She just left me.

677
00:34:44,080 --> 00:34:45,100
非常突然
Out of the blue.

678
00:34:45,350 --> 00:34:49,740
有一天她说结束了  就到此为止了
You know, one day she just said it was over and that was it.

679
00:34:50,830 --> 00:34:51,540
是啊
Yeah.

680
00:34:53,050 --> 00:34:54,070
那很痛苦
That's hard.

681
00:34:56,200 --> 00:34:59,290
不久前我也经历了类似的情况
I went through something similar not that long ago.

682
00:34:59,870 --> 00:35:00,750
真的吗
Oh, really?

683
00:35:00,760 --> 00:35:02,110
其实就是我今晚说的
Sort of what I was talking about tonight

684
00:35:02,110 --> 00:35:04,760
我经历的艰难时期
with the hard time I had been through.

685
00:35:04,870 --> 00:35:05,800
发生了什么
What happened?

686
00:35:09,290 --> 00:35:10,350
老故事了
Ancient history.

687
00:35:11,450 --> 00:35:12,350
哪个男的离开了你吗
A guy left you?

688
00:35:14,250 --> 00:35:15,190
其实是女的
It was a woman.

689
00:35:20,690 --> 00:35:24,680
我想我还没有完全放下  但时间会治愈一切嘛
I guess I'm not completely over it, but time heals, you know?

690
00:35:26,870 --> 00:35:28,690
我得回家了  很高兴认识你  麦克斯
I gotta get home, but it was nice to meet you, Max.

691
00:35:28,690 --> 00:35:30,110
很高兴认识你  丽萨
Nice meeting you, Lisa.

692
00:35:39,750 --> 00:35:41,250
能重新安排一下吗  我看看
Can we reschedule? Let me see.

693
00:35:41,670 --> 00:35:44,510
嗯  能把那个提前半小时吗
Yeah, yeah. Can you move that up by a half an hour?

694
00:35:46,630 --> 00:35:47,480
你好
Hello?

695
00:35:47,860 --> 00:35:49,370
现在方便吗  邓巴女士
Is this a good time, Ms. Dunbar?

696
00:35:49,580 --> 00:35:50,560
你是哪位
Who is this?

697
00:35:51,070 --> 00:35:52,160
道格·斯坦普
Doug Stamper.

698
00:35:53,790 --> 00:35:55,080
你怎么拿到这个号码的
How did you get this number?

699
00:35:55,740 --> 00:35:58,240
拿到号码很简单  你应该问的是
Phone numbers are easy. What you should be asking

700
00:35:58,240 --> 00:36:00,820
我怎么知道你今晚要跟吉阿罗参议员见面
is how I knew you were meeting with Senator Giallo tonight.

701
00:36:02,410 --> 00:36:03,480
回头看走廊
Look down the hallway.

702
00:36:07,640 --> 00:36:09,070
你们先走  我到下面找你们
Go ahead. I'll meet you down there.

703
00:36:09,070 --> 00:36:09,870
好吧
All right.

704
00:36:12,310 --> 00:36:13,770
别过来  待在原地
No. Stay where you are.

705
00:36:14,250 --> 00:36:15,910
我们不能被别人看到在一起
We wouldn't want to be seen together.

706
00:36:17,960 --> 00:36:19,460
总统派你来的吗
Did the president send you?

707
00:36:20,540 --> 00:36:23,530
不是  我们不联系了
No. He and I aren't in touch.

708
00:36:24,300 --> 00:36:25,520
那你为什么来这里
Then why are you here?

709
00:36:25,710 --> 00:36:28,950
你要组竞选团队  我想加入
You're forming your team. I want to be a part of it.

710
00:36:28,950 --> 00:36:30,040
真实原因呢
The real reason.

711
00:36:30,610 --> 00:36:31,810
这就是原因
That is the reason.

712
00:36:32,470 --> 00:36:34,850
他派你来的  别骗我
He sent you. Don't lie to me.

713
00:36:37,670 --> 00:36:40,050
我已经九个月没参与任何事了  邓巴女士
I've been out of the game for nine months, Ms. Dunbar.

714
00:36:40,540 --> 00:36:41,750
我想重回战局
I want to get back in.

715
00:36:42,470 --> 00:36:43,350
你要组建竞选团队
You're forming your team,

716
00:36:43,350 --> 00:36:45,010
我想成为开朝一员
and I want to get in on the ground floor.

717
00:36:47,280 --> 00:36:48,750
光有领导层还不够
The leadership isn't enough.

718
00:36:52,000 --> 00:36:53,390
你还需要基层人士
You need the rank and file.

719
00:36:54,020 --> 00:36:56,780
他们与各市县权力掮客的关系
Their connections to county and municipal power brokers.

720
00:36:57,520 --> 00:36:58,980
从初选开始到全面展开
The chiefs of a thousand kingdoms

721
00:36:58,980 --> 00:37:01,740
每一场选举中的当权人物
in every primary from Iowa to Super Tuesday.

722
00:37:02,710 --> 00:37:04,760
我在党鞭办公室工作了十年
I worked in the whip's office for ten years.

723
00:37:04,970 --> 00:37:07,050
我手上有每个人的资料
I have files on every single member.

724
00:37:07,640 --> 00:37:11,430
他们要什么  跟谁睡  中午吃什么
What they want, who they sleep with, what they eat for lunch.

725
00:37:11,840 --> 00:37:13,200
我对你会很有价值
I can be valuable to you.

726
00:37:13,920 --> 00:37:16,480
你怎么知道我今晚要跟吉阿罗见面
How did you know I was meeting with Giallo tonight?

727
00:37:16,910 --> 00:37:18,750
你跟领导层来往密切
You rub shoulders with the leadership.

728
00:37:18,860 --> 00:37:21,070
我跟为他们工作的人来往密切
I rub shoulders with the people who work for them.

729
00:37:27,470 --> 00:37:30,200
考虑一下吧  邓巴女士  我只有这点请求
Think about it, Ms. Dunbar. That's all I ask.

730
00:37:30,200 --> 00:37:31,250
下楼
Going down.

731
00:37:37,590 --> 00:37:38,990
我犯了个错误
I made a mistake.

732
00:37:39,640 --> 00:37:42,240
她在总统办公室里跟我说话的方式
I mean, the way she spoke to me in the Oval,

733
00:37:42,240 --> 00:37:43,860
让我恨不得勒死她
I wanted to strangle her.

734
00:37:45,120 --> 00:37:46,680
她到底在想什么
I mean, what is she thinking?

735
00:37:47,090 --> 00:37:48,590
跟在职总统竞争
Running against an incumbent

736
00:37:48,590 --> 00:37:50,940
我都提出给她最高法的职位了
when I offered her a seat on the court--

737
00:37:50,950 --> 00:37:53,480
博奇向她吹耳边风时  她就决定要参选了
She was going to run the moment Birch whispered in her ear.

738
00:37:53,710 --> 00:37:55,490
人一旦开始想象自己坐在总统办公室里
Once people imagine themselves in the Oval,

739
00:37:55,490 --> 00:37:56,540
就不会再回头了
there's no turning back.

740
00:37:56,540 --> 00:37:58,170
你跟他们一样清楚
You know that as well as anybody.

741
00:37:58,260 --> 00:38:01,640
是我自己的错  不应该给雅各布斯留选择余地
It's my own damn fault. Shouldn't have given Jacobs the choice.

742
00:38:01,640 --> 00:38:04,230
我应该在问她之前就宣布提名
I should've just announced her nomination before I even asked her.

743
00:38:04,230 --> 00:38:05,820
-需要我回家吗  -不用
- Should I come home? - No.

744
00:38:07,410 --> 00:38:09,990
我只需要考虑一下  理清思路
I just need to think. I need to clear my head.

745
00:38:10,780 --> 00:38:12,000
我能做点什么
Tell me what I can do.

746
00:38:15,680 --> 00:38:17,360
我为什么要有所保留
Why did I hold back?

747
00:38:18,410 --> 00:38:20,800
我为什么要对雅各布斯留情
Why did I show Jacobs any mercy?

748
00:38:20,800 --> 00:38:23,070
弗兰西斯  这可不像你的作风
Francis, this doesn't sound like you.

749
00:38:23,980 --> 00:38:26,520
把这些抛在脑后  想想下一步怎么做
Put this behind you. Think about what's next.

750
00:38:28,940 --> 00:38:30,770
是因为默罕默德
It was because of Mahmoud.

751
00:38:32,660 --> 00:38:34,210
我让他影响了我
I let him get to me.

752
00:38:36,540 --> 00:38:40,220
那些士兵灵柩上的国旗
And all those flags on those coffins and those soldiers, whose--

753
00:38:40,980 --> 00:38:43,790
我调派  又下葬了他们  是我的...
I deployed and then I buried in the ground. It's my--

754
00:38:43,790 --> 00:38:46,680
别说了  这帮不上忙
Stop it. This isn't doing you any good.

755
00:38:46,680 --> 00:38:48,960
你想谈的话我可以跟你谈
I will talk about this with you if you want,

756
00:38:49,220 --> 00:38:51,280
但我不允许你怀疑自己
but if you're doubting yourself, I can't indulge that.

757
00:38:51,280 --> 00:38:52,790
是啊  你说得对
No, you're right, of course.

758
00:38:54,120 --> 00:38:55,430
明早再谈吧
Well, let's talk in the morning.

759
00:38:55,430 --> 00:38:57,360
-有需要随时找我  -我知道
- I'm here if you need me. - I know.

760
00:38:59,510 --> 00:39:02,230
-晚安  -晚安  弗兰西斯
- Good night. - Good night, Francis.

761
00:39:26,600 --> 00:39:29,650
能帮我接艾迪斯主教吗
Yes, can you reach out to Bishop Eddis for me?

762
00:39:30,400 --> 00:39:31,280
我等着
I'll hold.

763
00:39:52,520 --> 00:39:53,600
谢谢  密查姆
Thank you, Meechum.

764
00:39:53,950 --> 00:39:56,280
-让我们单独谈谈  -好的
- If we can have some privacy. - Yes, sir.

765
00:39:58,710 --> 00:40:00,330
还骑博纳维尔呢
Still riding the Bonneville?

766
00:40:01,130 --> 00:40:04,430
把67款卖了换了派普伯恩  那车不错
Sold the '67 for a Pipeburn. Beautiful bike.

767
00:40:04,430 --> 00:40:06,530
有机会带我兜一圈
You should take me for a spin sometime.

768
00:40:07,070 --> 00:40:08,100
算了吧
I don't think so.

769
00:40:08,610 --> 00:40:09,890
骑那个太找死
They're a death wish.

770
00:40:10,670 --> 00:40:12,890
至少你知道自己能上天堂
At least you know you have a place in heaven.

771
00:40:17,670 --> 00:40:19,190
有什么事  总统先生
What's on your mind, Mr. President?

772
00:40:20,140 --> 00:40:21,650
那天葬礼
The burial the other day.

773
00:40:22,430 --> 00:40:24,430
你谈到了亚伯拉罕和以撒
You talked about Abraham and Isaac.

774
00:40:24,430 --> 00:40:27,180
上帝献出了他唯一的儿子
God giving up his only Son.

775
00:40:27,770 --> 00:40:28,560
就跟你说说
Between you and me,

776
00:40:28,560 --> 00:40:30,970
我在阿灵顿总说那一套
that's the same sermon I always use at Arlington.

777
00:40:31,800 --> 00:40:33,170
安葬的士兵太多
You put enough soldiers in the ground,

778
00:40:33,170 --> 00:40:34,870
就懒得写新悼词了
you get tired of writing new ones.

779
00:40:36,940 --> 00:40:38,760
那是我第一次听
It was the first time I had heard it.

780
00:40:38,900 --> 00:40:40,130
肯定不是最后一次
Won't be the last.

781
00:40:42,080 --> 00:40:44,520
我想理解正义
I want to understand what justice is.

782
00:40:46,490 --> 00:40:47,530
这可不简单
That's a big one.

783
00:40:48,110 --> 00:40:49,050
我知道
I know.

784
00:40:51,510 --> 00:40:54,190
我们的正义是先辈创造的
There's our justice, the kind men create.

785
00:40:55,430 --> 00:40:58,270
以《十诫》之类的戒律为基础
We base it on things like the Ten Commandments.

786
00:40:59,450 --> 00:41:01,560
但文字总有不同的解读方法
But those can be read a million different ways.

787
00:41:02,900 --> 00:41:05,240
"不可杀人"说的倒是很明确
"Thou shalt not kill" seems pretty clear.

788
00:41:06,020 --> 00:41:08,830
说得轻巧  我们不杀人
Who's to say? If we didn't kill,

789
00:41:09,620 --> 00:41:11,540
也许还有别人开杀戒
others would kill instead of us.

790
00:41:12,510 --> 00:41:14,200
《圣经》里谈了许多杀戮的故事
There's a lot of killing in the Bible.

791
00:41:15,020 --> 00:41:16,650
大卫王就是位勇士
King David was a warrior.

792
00:41:16,800 --> 00:41:20,560
那怎么用上帝给摩西的《十诫》解释他的行为呢
How do you reconcile that with the laws that God gave Moses?

793
00:41:21,440 --> 00:41:23,680
《十诫》也可以有不同解读
Even those laws require interpretation.

794
00:41:25,390 --> 00:41:28,280
有两条一定要记牢
There are two laws we have to remember above all else.

795
00:41:30,550 --> 00:41:33,730
他要我们爱上帝
He tells us to love God

796
00:41:34,130 --> 00:41:35,350
还要互敬互爱
and to love each other.

797
00:41:37,610 --> 00:41:39,820
怎么去爱你杀的人
You can't love the people you kill.

798
00:41:41,080 --> 00:41:42,430
当然可以
You sure as hell can.

799
00:41:43,010 --> 00:41:45,470
想杀你的人  你也要去爱
And you have to love the people who are trying to kill you.

800
00:41:47,330 --> 00:41:48,730
耶稣也爱罗马人
Jesus loved the Romans.

801
00:41:49,510 --> 00:41:50,730
他说  "天父  原谅他们吧
"Father, forgive them," He said,

802
00:41:50,740 --> 00:41:52,340
他们并不清楚自己的所作所为"
"For they know not what they do."

803
00:41:53,920 --> 00:41:55,220
他为什么不反抗
Why didn't he fight?

804
00:41:55,830 --> 00:41:58,570
他为什么自愿牺牲
Why did he allow himself to be sacrificed?

805
00:42:00,010 --> 00:42:02,210
我自问过许多遍
I ask myself that question a lot.

806
00:42:02,380 --> 00:42:04,830
我理解《旧约》的上帝
I understand the Old Testament God,

807
00:42:04,830 --> 00:42:06,290
权力至高无上
whose power is absolute,

808
00:42:06,290 --> 00:42:09,660
用恐惧统治人类  但是他...
who rules through fear, but... him.

809
00:42:16,440 --> 00:42:19,310
人类无法拥有至高无上的权力
There's no such thing as absolute power for us,

810
00:42:19,430 --> 00:42:21,380
只能接受上帝的统治
except on the receiving end.

811
00:42:22,270 --> 00:42:24,240
用恐惧统治不会有好下场
Using fear will get you nowhere.

812
00:42:24,400 --> 00:42:26,940
你的工作不是裁决正义
It's not your job to determine what's just.

813
00:42:27,370 --> 00:42:30,950
你也无权决定喜欢哪个上帝
It's not your place to choose the version of God you like best.

814
00:42:31,020 --> 00:42:32,910
你不必一个人效忠国家
It's not your duty to serve this country alone,

815
00:42:32,910 --> 00:42:35,910
也最好不要只想着为自己牟利
and it better not be your goal to simply serve yourself.

816
00:42:36,750 --> 00:42:37,950
你效忠主
You serve the Lord.

817
00:42:38,610 --> 00:42:40,560
通过他效忠众生
And through Him, you serve others.

818
00:42:42,000 --> 00:42:43,090
两条规则
Two rules.

819
00:42:43,640 --> 00:42:46,110
爱上帝  互敬互爱
Love God. Love each other.

820
00:42:46,880 --> 00:42:47,810
就这样
Period.

821
00:42:49,270 --> 00:42:51,080
你不是救世主  总统先生
You weren't chosen, Mr. President.

822
00:42:54,490 --> 00:42:55,610
他才是
Only he was.

823
00:43:02,690 --> 00:43:04,360
我能单独待一会儿吗
May I have a few moments?

824
00:43:04,670 --> 00:43:07,610
一个人待着  祈祷
For myself. To pray.

825
00:43:10,470 --> 00:43:11,490
可以啊
It's all yours.

826
00:43:45,010 --> 00:43:45,950
爱
Love?

827
00:43:47,210 --> 00:43:48,570
你就想推销这个吗
That's what you're selling?

828
00:43:52,930 --> 00:43:54,570
我不要
Well, I don't buy it.

829
00:44:19,420 --> 00:44:20,660
没事吧  先生
Is everything all right, sir?

830
00:44:22,560 --> 00:44:25,090
我在祈祷  他突然倒了
I was praying and it just fell.

831
00:44:50,190 --> 00:44:51,970
找个人清理一下
Please have someone clean this up.

832
00:44:52,850 --> 00:44:53,870
好的  先生
Yes, sir.

833
00:44:54,980 --> 00:44:56,580
这下我有上帝的耳朵了[上帝肯听我的了]
Well, I've got God's ear now.

834
00:44:58,140 --> 00:45:08,140
{\an5}{\pos(193,145)}奥巴马2008年大选期间对小布什的反恐政策有很多批评
但当选总统后  他在国家安全和反恐政策上
并没有完全放弃小布什政府在反恐事务中的鹰派主张
虽然奥巴马下令美军和情报机构
不许再对被俘的恐怖嫌犯进行"水刑"等逼供措施
但同时也下令扩大在中东地区进行无人机"定点打击"的军事行为
在过去几年中  无人机轰炸
成为奥巴马清除中东恐怖嫌犯的主要手段
这个政策在美国国内招致来自民主党左派
和共和党自由意志派人士的广泛反对
一些民间人权组织不断出版报告称美军行为造成大量无辜民众伤亡

835
00:45:23,140 --> 00:45:33,140
{\an5}{\pos(193,145)}2013年3月  美国司法部长霍德发表声明称
在未经适当司法程序前提下  在美国境内使用无人机
对美国籍恐怖嫌犯进行打击是违宪的
但是霍德没有说在境外进行无人机打击是违宪行为
司法部长霍德的声明发表后  来自肯塔基州的共和党参议员
著名的自由意志派政客兰德·保罗
在国会进行了长达13个小时的马拉松式演讲
其主题就是抗议美军出动无人机定点消灭美国籍的恐怖分子
他认为无论在国内还是国外
未经司法程序针对美国公民的无人机打击都是违宪的

